00:19:05.270 --> 00:19:07.940
And if not everyone in the
group has to join the union,

00:19:07.940 --> 00:19:11.430
then you've got a free rider
problem where people can say,

00:19:11.430 --> 00:19:16.490
oh, I'm a libertarian, I don't
believe in unions' bullshit.

00:19:16.490 --> 00:19:18.800
Well, they want you give
back half of your pay.

00:19:18.800 --> 00:19:22.070
You're enjoying the benefits
of having union representation,

00:19:22.070 --> 00:19:24.170
but you just don't
want to pay your share.

00:19:24.170 --> 00:19:27.300
I'm giving the unions
point of view obviously.

00:19:27.300 --> 00:19:30.170
So are the what--

00:19:30.170 --> 00:19:32.320
AUDIENCE: I said
or you're Ayn Rand.

00:19:32.320 --> 00:19:33.950
FREDERICK SALVUCCI: Oh, OK.

00:19:33.950 --> 00:19:35.930
So anyway, you get--

00:19:40.300 --> 00:19:48.310
so you get this situation
where we hypothesized that--

00:19:50.920 --> 00:19:55.810
right to work laws passed
in a lot of states,

00:19:55.810 --> 00:19:58.120
and didn't pass in
a lot of states.

00:19:58.120 --> 00:20:01.670
And they did not pass
and states surprisingly,

00:20:01.670 --> 00:20:02.770
that have strong unions.

00:20:02.770 --> 00:20:06.100
And they did pass in
the South and in places

00:20:06.100 --> 00:20:08.650
where they weren't, where there
wasn't much political power

00:20:08.650 --> 00:20:09.420
on union side.

00:20:09.420 --> 00:20:13.750
So we said, well, maybe that's
a proxy for the political power

00:20:13.750 --> 00:20:15.340
of unions.

00:20:15.340 --> 00:20:20.590
So have Javier took the right to
work states, separated them out

00:20:20.590 --> 00:20:27.650
from the states where union
membership is a requirement.

00:20:27.650 --> 00:20:32.030
And lo and behold, yes
there's a bigger premium

00:20:32.030 --> 00:20:38.330
on top of Baumol in the states
that are more union culture.

00:20:38.330 --> 00:20:40.790
And the states that are
more anti-union in culture,

00:20:40.790 --> 00:20:42.410
there's less of a
premium being paid.

00:20:42.410 --> 00:20:46.910
So it looks from the
data like this guess

00:20:46.910 --> 00:20:50.390
as to what's going on is at
least consistent with what

00:20:50.390 --> 00:20:51.680
the data says.

00:20:51.680 --> 00:20:55.590
Javier you added a couple
of nice papers on it.

00:20:55.590 --> 00:20:59.760
So then the next question
is, so what do you,

00:20:59.760 --> 00:21:01.600
what do you do about this?

00:21:01.600 --> 00:21:04.470
AUDIENCE: So is
there anything else

00:21:04.470 --> 00:21:08.240
that's like the government
when they give jobs

00:21:08.240 --> 00:21:10.590
