00:22:05.620 --> 00:22:07.070
And I'm paying his salary.

00:22:07.070 --> 00:22:10.510
And so it's not
particularly convenient,

00:22:10.510 --> 00:22:14.020
even for a somewhat
left-wing politician

00:22:14.020 --> 00:22:19.262
to want to pay higher
pays, other than the fact

00:22:19.262 --> 00:22:21.220
that especially if they're
from a district that

00:22:21.220 --> 00:22:23.440
has a lot of bus
drivers, then they

00:22:23.440 --> 00:22:25.130
want to take care of
that constituency.

00:22:25.130 --> 00:22:29.590
So there's the kind of
client-based politics

00:22:29.590 --> 00:22:33.320
that drives some politicians
in that direction.

00:22:33.320 --> 00:22:36.640
But a sort of general
left leaning attitude

00:22:36.640 --> 00:22:40.450
wouldn't particularly argue
to pay transit workers higher

00:22:40.450 --> 00:22:42.327
than teachers.

00:22:42.327 --> 00:22:44.410
But transit workers make
more money than teachers.

00:22:44.410 --> 00:22:48.760
So I mean it's a
pretty weird situation.

00:22:48.760 --> 00:22:50.950
And you keep peeling
away the onion

00:22:50.950 --> 00:22:53.410
saying what's really
going on here.

00:22:53.410 --> 00:22:56.380
And it looks like A, Baumol's
disease is a real problem.

00:22:56.380 --> 00:22:59.730
And B, there is this premium
on top of Baumol's disease

00:22:59.730 --> 00:23:02.110
that comes out of the nature
of the political process,

00:23:02.110 --> 00:23:04.900
and the extra bargaining
that labor has.

00:23:04.900 --> 00:23:09.250
So labor has bargaining of the
normal kind that a union always

00:23:09.250 --> 00:23:12.790
has with an employer,
because they

00:23:12.790 --> 00:23:14.710
control the supply of labor.

00:23:14.710 --> 00:23:17.050
But then it has this
political dimension.

00:23:17.050 --> 00:23:22.210
So once the enterprise becomes
dependent on political support

00:23:22.210 --> 00:23:26.010
for subsidy, labor now
has to bite of the apple.

00:23:26.010 --> 00:23:30.740
And I think it makes
sense as a theory.

00:23:30.740 --> 00:23:33.430
Looks like the data supported
it from Javier's research.

00:23:33.430 --> 00:23:34.556
Yes?

