00:26:17.950 --> 00:26:20.030
The objective is
not to reduce costs.

00:26:20.030 --> 00:26:23.660
The objective is to improve
what you're offering people,

00:26:23.660 --> 00:26:24.160
I think.

00:26:24.160 --> 00:26:29.300
If you want your product
to be prized, and still

00:26:29.300 --> 00:26:31.460
around in 10 years,
as opposed to just

00:26:31.460 --> 00:26:33.590
being a temporary Band-Aid.

00:26:33.590 --> 00:26:36.000
But there are different
philosophies of management.

00:26:36.000 --> 00:26:38.570
But in either case,
whether you're

00:26:38.570 --> 00:26:41.390
looking at a cost
reduction type strategy,

00:26:41.390 --> 00:26:44.690
or whether you're looking
at a value maximization,

00:26:44.690 --> 00:26:47.600
productivity and efficiency are
important things to look to.

00:26:47.600 --> 00:26:51.440
So that's such one kind
of thing you should

00:26:51.440 --> 00:26:52.910
be involved in all the time.

00:26:55.840 --> 00:27:04.800
And you could also
think about what

00:27:04.800 --> 00:27:11.700
are the external factors that
might lead transit to become

00:27:11.700 --> 00:27:15.335
more valuable over time.

00:27:19.250 --> 00:27:22.510
Even if you're not being
particularly more efficient

00:27:22.510 --> 00:27:25.090
in the way you're delivering it.

00:27:25.090 --> 00:27:30.100
So if the metropolitan
area is growing,

00:27:30.100 --> 00:27:37.050
and if transit is also
growing, then the cost

00:27:37.050 --> 00:27:42.210
per rider or the subsidy
provider should go down.

00:27:42.210 --> 00:27:47.500
Because you've got less empty
seats, that's the nice version.

00:27:47.500 --> 00:27:50.850
You've got more crowded buses,
the not so nice version.

00:27:50.850 --> 00:27:56.280
But you can get
more service, if you

00:27:56.280 --> 00:27:59.190
don't look too hard at the
quality of that service,

00:27:59.190 --> 00:28:02.830
at lower cost as the system
gets more and more customers.

00:28:02.830 --> 00:28:07.350
So growth in passengers
is certainly benign.

00:28:07.350 --> 00:28:09.780
Now too much of a good
thing is a bad thing.

00:28:09.780 --> 00:28:13.470
You get the kind of crowding
you're studying in Chicago.

00:28:13.470 --> 00:28:15.949
That doesn't seem quite
efficient when people can't of

00:28:15.949 --> 00:28:18.240
get on, and are being left
behind, and everything else.

00:28:18.240 --> 00:28:21.420
But from the point of view
of the green eyeshade guys,

00:28:21.420 --> 00:28:23.670
that are just looking at
the numbers, the more people

00:28:23.670 --> 00:28:29.310
you cram onto the vehicles
that's dampening down

00:28:29.310 --> 00:28:30.370
the subsidy a bit.

00:28:30.370 --> 00:28:36.510
So even with no particular
management, effort, or skill,

00:28:36.510 --> 00:28:38.430
if the region happens
to be growing,

00:28:38.430 --> 00:28:42.450
and if transit ridership
happens to be growing,

00:28:42.450 --> 00:28:46.350
then the value of the
transit is growing.

00:28:46.350 --> 00:28:53.770
And that can offset the
Baumol's problem to some degree.

00:28:53.770 --> 00:28:59.180
And if you think of what
the competing mode is.

00:28:59.180 --> 00:29:02.990
If the area is growing
and the jobs are growing,

00:29:02.990 --> 00:29:06.050
and the congestion on
the roadways are growing,

00:29:06.050 --> 00:29:09.710
conditions that certainly
apply here and in Chicago.

00:29:09.710 --> 00:29:12.980
Then the societal
value of the transit

00:29:12.980 --> 00:29:17.600
is higher, both for
the riders because

00:29:17.600 --> 00:29:22.120
their alternative choice
is to be in the congestion.

00:29:22.120 --> 00:29:24.260
And for the drivers
who don't use transit

00:29:24.260 --> 00:29:26.540
who are in the
congested conditions who

00:29:26.540 --> 00:29:29.090
are happy to have some
people out of their way.

00:29:29.090 --> 00:29:33.110
So through no virtue
of the transit manager,

00:29:33.110 --> 00:29:36.410
if the regions are growing
and ridership is growing,

00:29:36.410 --> 00:29:40.640
that can help offset
the Baumol's disease.

00:29:40.640 --> 00:29:43.480
Both in the practical sense
of getting more revenue,

00:29:43.480 --> 00:29:47.780
and in the theoretical sense
that the value of the transit

00:29:47.780 --> 00:29:50.750
collective product
is actually going up,

00:29:50.750 --> 00:29:54.030
through no virtue of your own.

