00:46:03.210 --> 00:46:04.420
You have one player.

00:46:04.420 --> 00:46:08.560
So that one player you'd
be subsidizing more,

00:46:08.560 --> 00:46:11.400
potentially pay more rent
to the employer rather than

00:46:11.400 --> 00:46:12.600
the employees.

00:46:12.600 --> 00:46:16.380
Because that one employer has
a lot of leverage over you

00:46:16.380 --> 00:46:18.590
to drive up the amount
you get paid overtime.

00:46:18.590 --> 00:46:19.590
FREDERICK SALVUCCI: Yes.

00:46:19.590 --> 00:46:22.530
So that's very insightful.

00:46:22.530 --> 00:46:24.930
And that's fairly accurate.

00:46:24.930 --> 00:46:28.590
What the data shows that
Javier pulled together

00:46:28.590 --> 00:46:34.680
is that contracting out
does reduce cost somewhat.

00:46:34.680 --> 00:46:41.100
But that in comparison to places
that provide all bus service

00:46:41.100 --> 00:46:43.350
